  "prompt": "What is a psychiatrist?",
  "response": "A psychiatrist is a medical doctor who specializes in the diagnosis, treatment, and prevention of mental health disorders. Psychiatrists have completed medical school and a residency in psychiatry, which equips them with the knowledge to understand the complex relationship between emotional, psychological, and physical health.\n\nPsychiatrists can prescribe medication, conduct psychotherapy, and provide various forms of treatment for mental health conditions such as depression, anxiety, schizophrenia, bipolar disorder, and more. They may work in various settings, including hospitals, private practices, clinics, and research institutions, often collaborating with other health care professionals to offer comprehensive care for their patients.",
